                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14455841" author="agudian" created="Sat, 13 Jul 2013 17:50:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed. All SCM-URLs on the sites are pinned down to &lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/maven-surefire.git&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/maven-surefire.git&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;, an update to latest version of maven-project-info-reports-plugin also improves the text displayed for GIT.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456014" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sat, 13 Jul 2013 18:28:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The website still shows the wrong link.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455920" author="agudian" created="Sat, 13 Jul 2013 18:38:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Didn&apos;t mention it explicitly: it&apos;ll be up with the next release, which will be done &quot;soon&quot; after Kristian got around fixing the encoding issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455960" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sat, 13 Jul 2013 18:51:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it not possible to fix the website between releases?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I thought easy website publication was part of the idea of svnpubsub.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455978" author="agudian" created="Sun, 14 Jul 2013 05:43:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is possible, but quite some time effort. As the next release isn&apos;t too far away, I&apos;d like to spare the hassle. The fork-me-on-GitHub ribbons on each page also provide a convenient alternative for users.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456045" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sun, 14 Jul 2013 06:00:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s no need to republish the whole site.&lt;br/&gt;
Since the site is in SVN &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, it would be possible to fix just the URLs.&lt;br/&gt;
This will get overridden by the next republish, but that won&apos;t matter.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn-master.apache.org/repos/infra/websites/production/maven/content/surefire/maven-failsafe-plugin/source-repository.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn-master.apache.org/repos/infra/websites/production/maven/content/surefire/maven-failsafe-plugin/source-repository.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17994414" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:21:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1577&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1577&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
